Abdomen
. Cerci (Fig. 
34
) comparatively long for the group; with a short and apically incurved tooth; wide prior to tooth, but getting narrow after it; widely incurved distal to tooth. Tenth tergite (Fig. 
28
) transverse and with a wide medial projection. Subgenital plate as in genus, with a shallow triangular incision and rounded apical lobes, styli small. Titillators (Fig. 
40
) as in species group, basal arms almost twice of apical arms and apical arms with spines along a margin dorsally.

Distribution . The new species occurs in alpine zone of the Tendürek Mts. Located between Ağrı and Van provinces in north-east Turkey (
Fig. 1
).
